 or less; (b) subsequent to that determination the applicant’s capital rises to more than £16,000; and (c) the increase occurs whilst there is in force an assessed income period within the meaning of sections 6 and 9 of the State Pension Credit Act 2002. (6) the higher amount of full disregard in respect of this scheme for any of the following - (a) a war disablement (b) a war widow’s pension or war widower’s pension;

